                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d814">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/945: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-14T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 14, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Your 11, May 7, noon.<note n="14" xml:id="d814fn14">Not printed.</note> The
                    Department approached British Embassy on May 11 along lines suggested in your
                    paragraph 4.</p>
                <p>Have you any mental reservations which would cause us to delay recognition? If
                    not, I purpose to request authority from the President to recognize the Barclay
                    régime shortly after you telegraph me that the Liberian Congress has withdrawn
                    its repudiationist legislation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
